Our leaders are seasoned conference speakers and contributors to top supply chain publications—especially around freight operations, technology and logistics strategy.   As ASCM reimagines its flagship event with a focus on innovation and transformation, we’d love to contribute a session that highlights how transportation strategy and logistics execution must evolve in tandem. Hello, I hope you’re doing well. I’m reaching out on behalf of Samsung SDS / Caidentia as we begin planning our event participation for 2026.  We’re active members of the DSCI community and were grateful for the opportunity to participate in CHAINge this year, including Ian Silver’s speaking session, which was facilitated through our DSCI membership and collaboration. It was a great experience, and we appreciated the opportunity to contribute to the program.  With Nick Vyas stepping into the ASCM Chairman role for 2026, and given that members of our leadership team know Nick through his work with the Kendrick Global Supply Chain Institute at the USC Marshall School of Business, we’re interested in exploring how Samsung SDS might be meaningfully involved in CHAINge 2026. Specifically, we’d love to learn more about potential speaking sessions and sponsorship opportunities.  At this stage, we’re in an exploratory phase and would appreciate any information you can share regarding available sponsorship options, speaking tracks, timelines, and next steps.  Thank you! We truly value the partnership and look forward to continuing the conversation.  Best regards, Amy Rios, Marketing Programs & Events Manager, Samsung SDS | Caidentia
